NetFortris CTO Tom Swayze to Speak at GENBAND Perspectives16
[May 03, 2016]
NetFortris CTO Tom Swayze to Speak at GENBAND Perspectives16
Tweet
ORLANDO, Fla., May 3, 2016 /PRNewswire/ --NetFortris, Inc., a leading provider of unified communications as a service (UCaaS), today announced that CTO Tom Swayze will join a panel of unified communication experts to define and discuss industry trends, key enterprise customer requirements and success factors at GENBAND Perspectives16. On the one-year anniversary of NetFortris' adoption of the GENBAND UC platform and hundreds of successful customer installations, Swayze will address some of the pressing trends and essential UC technologies enterprises are leveraging to support today's hyper-connected mobile workforce.
Attendees of Swayze's session will learn about the rapidly evolving enterprise dynamics and mobile conveniences that are driving demand for secure UC communications and network solutions. The audience will gain strategic and tactical insights to help them design effective unified communications systems that meet the needs of demanding, on-the-go employees and customers. Key panel topics include:
How cloud solutions are replacing aging on premise PBXs to meet the needs of mobile users and to realize cost and productivity efficiencies.
A discussion about competitive technology strategies including office suites integrated with unified communications functionality.
How to give IT a technology foundation for more advanced application and functionality they may require in the future.
What: UC Keynote Panel at GENBAND Perspectives16When: Tuesday, May 3, 2016 2:35 p.m. Where:JW Marriott Orlando, Grande Lakes 4040 Central Florida Parkway Orlando, Florida 32837
Myron Wallace, NetFortris Director of Unified Communications Engineering, will participate in a break out session detailing the technical issues with designing and implementing a UC solution based on the GENBAND Application Server platform. Mr. Wallace's session will be held in the Med 1 breakout room on May 4, at 4:30 p.m.
About NetFortris, Inc. NetFortris provides secure cloud-based voice and data communications solutions, hosted productivity and specialized applications, and business devices to enterprises. The NetFortris Cloud Communications Platform (CCP) serves as a central foundation for all NetFortris services, and delivers enterprise-class security, analytics, and management for simple, scalable and highly secure operations. NetFortris is based San Francisco, California and is privately held. For more information, please visit http://www.netfortris.comor call 888-469-5100.
About GENBANDGENBAND is a global leader in real time communications software solutions for service providers, enterprises, independent software vendors, systems integrators and developers in over 80 countries. The company's Network Modernization, Unified Communications, Mobility and Embedded Communications solutions enable its customers to quickly capitalize on growing market segments and introduce differentiating products, applications and services. GENBAND's market-leading solutions, which are deployable in the network, on premise or through the cloud, help its customers connect people to each other and address the growing demands of today's consumers and businesses for real time communications wherever they happen to be. To learn more visit www.genband.com.
GENBAND, the GENBAND logo and icon are trademarks of GENBAND.
To view the original version on PR Newswire, visit:http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/netfortris-cto-tom-swayze-to-speak-at-genband-perspectives16-300261589.html
SOURCE NetFortris, Inc.
